Sure, here are several example sentences in Serbian that use the word "belo" in different forms and positions:

1. *Belo* jaje je pored crne kokoške. (The white egg is next to the black hen.)
2. Ja sam videla *belog* psa u parku. (I saw a white dog in the park.)
3. Da li ti se sviđa ova *bela* haljina? (Do you like this white dress?)
4. On je slikao *bele* ruže u bašti. (He painted white roses in the garden.)
5. *Belo* brašno nije zdravo za zube. (White flour is not healthy for your teeth.)
6. Jutros je bilo *belo* od snega. (This morning was white from the snow.)
7. *Bela* riba je veoma ukusna. (White fish is very tasty.)
8. *Beli* golub je simbol mira. (The white dove is a symbol of peace.)

Translation:

1. *Belo* jaje je pored crne kokoške. (The white egg is next to the black hen.)
2. Ja sam videla *belog* psa u parku. (I saw a white dog in the park.)
3. Da li ti se sviđa ova *bela* haljina? (Do you like this white dress?)
4. On je slikao *bele* ruže u bašti. (He painted white roses in the garden.)
5. *Belo* brašno nije zdravo za zube. (White flour is not healthy for your teeth.)
6. Jutros je bilo *belo* od snega. (This morning was white from the snow.)
7. *Bela* riba je veoma ukusna. (White fish is very tasty.)
8. *Beli* golub je simbol mira. (The white dove is a symbol of peace.)